			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Alkali is a soluble salt obtained from the ashes of plants and consisting largely of potassium or sodium carbonate. It is a substance having marked basic properties. Alkali metals include lithium (Li), sodium (Na), potassium (K), rubidium (Rb), cesium (Cs), and francium (Fr). They react with water to form alkalies, which are strong bases capable of neutralizing acids. Sodium hydroxide (NaOH) is the most widely used industrial alkali.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">碱是一种从植物灰烬中提取的可溶性盐，主要由碳酸钾或碳酸钠组成。它是一种具有明显碱性的物质。碱金属包括锂（Li）、钠（Na）、钾（K）、铷（Rb）、铯（Cs）和钫（Fr）。它们与水反应生成碱，碱是能中和酸的强碱。氢氧化钠（NaOH）是应用最广泛的工业碱。</common:generalComment>
